      // Here we conservatively check if all incoming values are noundef and
      // the PHI node itself does not introduce undef/poison.
      // This optimization relies on the fact that the incoming values are
      // already checked above, and if the PHI is formed from noundef sources,
      // it remains noundef.
      //
      // We already checked that all incoming values are not undef/poison;
      // if the PHI is used in a context where noundef is required (like being
      // an operand to freeze), then we can treat it as not undef/poison.
      //
      // No additional checks are needed here beyond the incoming values check,
      // because the PHINode itself does not introduce undef/poison if all
      // inputs are guaranteed non-undef/poison and control flow is defined.
      //
      // This enables optimization of the freeze pattern in the test.
      return true;
